Sentencas: The Fe, Ni-BaCe0.8Y0.2O3-delta, and Pt catalysts and Pt catalysts were used as the anodic materials of an intermediate-temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cell (SOFC) for direct utilization of dimethylether (DME) gas fuel.
Titulo: Development of the Fe Anodic Catalyst for Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Operated at Intermediate-temperature Direct Utilizing of Dimethylether Fuel

Sentencas: A proton conducting oxide BaCe0.8Y0.2O3-delta (BCY20) was used as the electrolyte (thickness 500 mu m) and a Pt was used as the cathode.
Titulo: Development of the Fe Anodic Catalyst for Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Operated at Intermediate-temperature Direct Utilizing of Dimethylether Fuel

Sentencas: The cell was operated at 600 degrees C.
Titulo: Development of the Fe Anodic Catalyst for Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Operated at Intermediate-temperature Direct Utilizing of Dimethylether Fuel

Sentencas: The maximum power density of the cell with the Fe anodic catalyst was 36.4 mW cm(-2) at 70 mA cm(-2), while the maximum power density of the cell with a Ni-BCY20 and the Pt anode were 5.5 mW cm(-2) at 10 mA cm(-2) and 8.4 mW cm(-2) at 20 mA cm(-2), respectively.
Titulo: Development of the Fe Anodic Catalyst for Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Operated at Intermediate-temperature Direct Utilizing of Dimethylether Fuel

Sentencas: DME was mainly decomposed to H-2, CO and CH4 by Fe anode.
Titulo: Development of the Fe Anodic Catalyst for Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Operated at Intermediate-temperature Direct Utilizing of Dimethylether Fuel

Sentencas: In this study, we investigated the process of anodic reactions with H-2 and CO fuel.
Titulo: Development of the Fe Anodic Catalyst for Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Operated at Intermediate-temperature Direct Utilizing of Dimethylether Fuel
